Subject: Re: [VB] Re: [T2] Fuel shut off solenoid?

On Sat, 30 Dec 2006, MyGroups wrote:

> My question would be is there any lag of the valve closing after the
> engine is shut off? I mean my brakes have 2-3 vacuum boosted pushes left
> in them after the engine is turned off.

The vacuum booster has a built-in reservoir to store vacuum.  This will
not affect a vacuum-operated valve as it taps from a different vacuum
source at the manifold.
